<br>
E- Greetings Mortiris and thank you for having us inside your beautifully...dark city.  We appreciate the lengths you had to go to get us into this part of the city.  Thanks goes out to your Queen as well.<br>
<br>
M - Thank you Eldrias and I must say it is an honor to have such a powerful and distinguished wizard here as well.  You have done quite well after your retirement.  Although if the one called Walli had referred to me as a &quot;man servant&quot;,  I do believe he would have awakened with a debilitating disease in the genital area.<br>
<br>
E- Hmmm....**whispers** we'll talk later.  Oh well Mortiris I don't think that is necessary.  After all, Walli is about to undergo the Joining of the Rings ceremony with Sylina Kyle.<br>
<br>
M - Yes.....lovely woman......would you care for some &quot;spiced&quot; wine?  Besides its exquisite taste, it also acts as a natural &quot;preservative.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
E- Uh NO thank you.  Well I am sure the viewers are looking forward to finding out more about you Mortiris, so let's get started.  Can I call you Morty?<br>
<br>
M  - Would you like to rot in a corpse's shell?<br>
<br>
E- <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->        &quot;In ya'll's neighborhood?'  <br>
<br>
M - What?<br>
<br>
E- Ahem...nothing.  So, Mortiris we know you were born here in Neriak, but tell us about your early days.<br>
<br>
M  - Well my mother, Pyye, is a priestess of Innothule and my father **mumble** is a warrior.<br>
<br>
E- Pardon?  I think we missed your father's name.  The viewers need to know, so don't hold back. I mean how bad could it be..<br>
<br>
M - OK...YOU PRYING DEVIL! MY FATHER IS VESILOUS!!  Damn you to the nine hells.<br>
<br>
**LONG PAUSE**<br>
<br>
E- Oh...well then...**aside** the ratings are gonna go through the roof on this one.  Ok well let's move beyond the whole family thing.  Tell us about how you became a necromancer.<br>
<br>
M  - I had a ghoul friend as a child.<br>
<br>
E- <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->       Gods! You are a riot! Hahaha<br>
<br>
M - What is so funny you hyena faced bastard?<br>
<br>
E- Nothing...nothing.  Ok well let's find out about your hobbies and such. What is your favorite hobby?<br>
<br>
M - Death and Resurrection.  And I like cooking....<br>
<br>
E- Favorite Color?<br>
<br>
M - Death<br>
<br>
E- Is that a new Crayola color I missed?<br>
<br>
M - No...death's form comes in myriad spectrums of death, rebirth, and debilitation.<br>
<br>
E- Yes but could you give us the ACTUAL color of death?<br>
<br>
M - By Innoruk's Chin!!   I guess it is a green mauve color!<br>
<br>
E- What is your favorite food?<br>
<br>
M - Manroot<br>
<br>
E - Really?  What a coincidence. I had a ranger friend named Hanselloch who used to give me manroot all the time.<br>
<br>
M - Really?.....interesting......<br>
<br>
E- Oh....that came out bad.  I meant he gave me the vegetable that we were discussing.<br>
<br>
M - Uh huh<br>
<br>
E- Ahem...well then.... time for a commercial break. We'll be right back. Stay tuned.<br>
<br>
***************************************************************************<br>
<br>
Fhozie: Hi Norrath!  Do you need Convincing of Something?  Sure we all do.  That is why I have opened the first Convince Store for all your Norrathian Convincing needs.  Wanna decide on buying that Fungi Tunic?  No problem. Stop by Fhozie's Walking Convinces Store and we'll make a believer out of YOU!!<br>
(See Fhozie's Bio to get the joke) **actually Fhozie has gone back and corrected the misspelling so you'll only catch the original typo here**<br>
****************************************************************************<br>
<br>
E- And we're back. So Mortiris what is your favorite spot to hunt?<br>
<br>
M - The deserts of Ro but actually necromancers are known for moving around a lot, so that one is difficult to answer.<br>
<br>
E- What do you do when you are depressed or stress?<br>
<br>
M  - I dig up old friends.<br>
<br>
E- <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      HAHAHA damn funny stuff there Mortiris?<br>
<br>
M - Why do you insist on laughing at every answer I give you?<br>
<br>
E- It's...funny...you know...when you.  Anyway, what are your aspirations?<br>
<br>
M - To spread hate in Innothule's name.  I personally like to bring back dead elven relatives and send them into Felwithe.  When they find their family's dwelling they scratch on the windows.  When the relatives open the window, the risen corpse of Uncle Pansy drops his pants and moons the family.  MWAHAHAHAHAH!  Well...laugh!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
E- **shivers** ha...ha...haha well at least you have SOME sense of humor. Any other future goals?<br>
<br>
M - To one day finish my training and join the ranks of members like Walli, Aeres, Macgarnacle and my.....father.<br>
<br>
E- Yes. They are all an outstanding group.  Well, that about wraps it up for this edition of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   E! Celebrity Hander Profile</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I want to thank my guest Mortiris for his time and thank you for joining us.  Good night and see you all next time.<br>
<br>
